            <p>
                The center of buoyancy (<InlineEquation equation="B" />) is the point where the total buoyant force on a 
                submerged or floating object acts. You can think of it as the center of gravity of 
                the volume of fluid displaced by the object. This term is crucial for understanding 
                stability and equilibrium in hydrodynamics. 
            </p>


